name: Leagues Cup
summary: Leagues Cup, a tournament featuring teams from Major League Soccer (MLS) and Liga MX, returns on July 26th with live coverage on Apple TV for the MLS Season Pass. In its 2024 edition, the Leagues Cup expands to a tournament format, launching with a group stage and featuring 47 clubs competing for a single-match championship game. Fans can find detailed information about the tournament on various MLS club websites, including SoundersFC.com, MLSsoccer.com, New England Revolution, and LAFC. USA Today provides an overview of the tournament, explaining its World Cup-style format, while Inter Miami CF, Orlando City SC, Atlanta United FC, and ESPN provide specific updates and match previews. Due to field conditions, the D.C. Leagues Cup game has been moved.

name: Tahiti
summary: The upcoming 2024 Paris Olympics will feature a unique surfing competition in Tahiti, an archipelago in the Pacific Ocean thousands of miles from Paris. The decision to hold the surfing events in Tahiti stems from the region's iconic waves, with Teahupo'o being a legendary surfing spot. The opening ceremony of the competition will celebrate Polynesian culture through traditional singing, ceremonies, and straw hats. Surfers will compete for Olympic medals in a floating Athlete Village, showcasing the sport's unique blend of athleticism and the natural environment. Competitors will navigate challenging waves and potentially dangerous conditions, requiring extensive preparation and safety measures. Despite the distance from Paris, the Tahiti surfing competition is expected to attract significant attention, with surfers keen to showcase their skills on one of the world's most renowned waves.
